# Bank Marketing Logistic Regression from Scratch

## Objective
The goal of this project was to build a binary logistic regression model from scratch using NumPy to predict whether a customer would subscribe to a term deposit.

## Workflow
- Loaded and inspected the Bank Marketing dataset
- Converted the target variable (`yes` / `no`) into binary form
- Identified numeric and categorical features
- Applied one-hot encoding to categorical columns
- Split the dataset into training and test sets
- Standardized features using training-set statistics only
- Implemented logistic regression from scratch with gradient descent
- Tuned the classification threshold to optimize F1 score

## Results
### Best threshold
- **0.22**

### Best performance
- **F1 score:** 0.5773
- **Precision:** 0.5376
- **Recall:** 0.6232

### Performance at default threshold (0.5)
- **F1 score:** 0.4429
- **Precision:** 0.6480
- **Recall:** 0.3365

## Conclusion
The model achieved a solid baseline performance and showed that threshold tuning was essential due to class imbalance. This project demonstrates a full end-to-end implementation of logistic regression without using built-in machine learning models.
